    q: 'Will I borrow less than an employed person on the same income?',
    a: 'Not for being self-employed in itself. The income multiple a lender applies is the same whether you are employed or self-employed, so any gap comes from how your income is assessed rather than the multiple. A conservative reading of your profit, or a lender that ignores retained profit, can trim the assessed figure, and the multiple is applied to that figure. Place the case with a lender that reads your structure fairly and the amount tends to reflect what you genuinely earn.',
